      <hedline>
        <hl1>Colonel's Wife Sentenced To 5 Years in Prison</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Laurie Ann Hiett, who admitted smuggling heroin from United States Embassy in Bogota, Colombia, to New York City, is sentenced to five years in prison (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The wife of the United States Army colonel who once ran the government's antidrug operations in Colombia was sentenced to five years in prison yesterday for smuggling heroin from Bogota to New York City through diplomatic mail.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The wife of the United States Army colonel who once ran the government's antidrug operations in Colombia was sentenced to five years in prison yesterday for smuggling heroin from Bogota to New York City through diplomatic mail.</p>
        <p>Laurie Ann Hiett pleaded guilty in January to sending six innocuous-looking brown packages filled with heroin from the United States Embassy in Bogota to Manhattan and Queens. Although for months she denied that her husband, Col. James C. Hiett, knew about her crimes, Colonel Hiett admitted last month that he had paid household bills with thousands of dollars that he knew his wife had earned from drug trafficking. He is to be sentenced in June.</p>
        <p>METRO NEWS BRIEFS: NEW YORK</p>
      </block>
